questions.question: What is a set?
questions.explanation: A set is a collection of objects.

questions.question: Which of the following is a finite set?
options: The set of all natural numbers
The set of all even numbers
The set of all prime numbers less than 10
questions.explanation: The set of all prime numbers less than 10 is a finite set.

questions.question: Which of the following is an infinite set?
options: The set of all natural numbers
The set of all prime numbers less than 10
The set of all even numbers less than 20
questions.explanation: The set of all natural numbers is an infinite set.

questions.question: What is the symbol for an empty set?
questions.explanation: The symbol for an empty set is {}.

questions.question: Which of the following sets is empty?
questions.explanation: The set {} is empty.

questions.question: What is the cardinality of the set {1, 2, 3, 4}?
questions.explanation: The cardinality of the set {1, 2, 3, 4} is 4.

questions.question: Which of the following sets is a subset of {1, 2, 3}?
questions.explanation: The set {1, 2} is a subset of {1, 2, 3}.

questions.question: What is the union of the sets {1, 2} and {2, 3}?
questions.explanation: The union of the sets {1, 2} and {2, 3} is {1, 2, 3}.

questions.question: What is the intersection of the sets {1, 2} and {2, 3}?
questions.explanation: The intersection of the sets {1, 2} and {2, 3} is {2}.

questions.question: What is the difference of the sets {1, 2, 3} and {2, 3}?
questions.explanation: The difference of the sets {1, 2, 3} and {2, 3} is {1}.

questions.question: Which of the following sets is a proper subset of {1, 2, 3}?
questions.explanation: The set {1, 2} is a proper subset of {1, 2, 3}.

questions.question: What is the power set of {1, 2}?
Which of the following sets is equal to {a, b, c}?
questions.explanation: The set {a, b, c} is equal to {a, b, c}.

questions.question: What is the complement of the set {1, 2} in the universal set {1, 2, 3, 4}?
questions.explanation: The complement of the set {1, 2} in the universal set {1, 2, 3, 4} is {3, 4}.

questions.question: Which of the following sets is disjoint with {1, 2, 3}?
questions.explanation: The set {4, 5} is disjoint with {1, 2, 3}.

questions.question: What is the Cartesian product of the sets {1, 2} and {a, b}?
questions.explanation: The Cartesian product of the sets {1, 2} and {a, b} is {(1, a), (1, b), (2, a), (2, b)}.

questions.question: Which of the following sets is a singleton set?
questions.explanation: The set {1} is a singleton set.

questions.question: What is the cardinality of the set {a, b, c, d}?
questions.explanation: The cardinality of the set {a, b, c, d} is 4.

questions.question: Which of the following sets is a subset of {1, 2, 3, 4}?

questions.question: What is the difference of the sets {a, b, c} and {b, c}?

questions.question: Which of the following sets is a proper subset of {a, b, c}?

questions.question: Which of the following sets is equal to {x, y, z}?
questions.explanation: The set {x, y, z} is equal to {x, y, z}.
